st Kata'ib Hezbollah]]\n| Mourning period began on New Year's Eve.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arabic.rt.com/middle_east/1072845-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%82%D8%AA%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B5%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A/|title=\u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062f\u0627\u062f \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642 3 \u0623\u064a\u0627\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0643\u064a|website=RT Arabic}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==2020s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|Iran}}\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| rowspan=2| 3\n| rowspan=2| Death of [[Qasem Soleimani]], commander of Iran's [[Quds Force]], in a [[2020 Baghdad International Airport airstrike|U.S. airstrike]] in [[Baghdad]], [[Iraq]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/news/article/Iraq-At-least-3-Katyusha-rockets-fired-at-14945882.php|title=US kills Iran's most powerful general in Baghdad airstrike|date=January 3, 2020|website=SFChronicle.com|access-date=January 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103053917/https://www.sfchronicle.com/news/article/Iraq-At-least-3-Katyusha-rockets-fired-at-14945882.php|archive-date=January 3, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Iraq}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraq-mourning-declared-for-soleimani-al-muhandis/1692521|title=Iraq: Mourning declared for Soleimani, al-Muhandis|website=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Iran}}\n| 2020\n| 1\n| Victims of the stampede at [[Funerals of Qasem Soleimani|Qasem Soleimani's funeral]] and the crash of [[Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arabic.sputniknews.com/world/202001081043988392-%D8%A5%D9%