ex|2012 Disaster at the Paraguana Refinery Complex]] ([[Venezuela]], 3 days)\n*Victims of the [[2013 Houphou\u00ebt-Boigny stampede]] (Ivory Coast, 3 days)\n*Victims of the [[Kiss nightclub fire|2013 Santa Maria nightclub fire]] (Brazil, 3 days)<ref name=\"BBC News Article\">{{cite news|title=Brazil mourns Santa Maria nightclub fire victims|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-21226565|accessdate=28 January 2013|date=2013-01-28|publisher=BBC News}}</ref>\n*Victims of the 2013 [[Torre Ejecutiva Pemex explosion|Pemex Executive Tower explosion]] ([[Mexico]], 3 days)<ref name=\"El Universal Article\">{{cite news|title=Pe\u00f1a Nieto decreed three days of national mourning. (Spanish)|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/900218.html|date=1 February 2013}}</ref>\n*Victims of the [[2013 Bulgarian protests against the first Borisov cabinet]] ([[Bulgaria]], 1 day)\n*Victims of the 2013 [[Santiago de Compostela derailment]] (Spain, 3 day)\n*Victims of [[Typhoon Haiyan (Yolanda)]]\n*Victims of the [[2013 Sardinia floods]] (22 November 2013, Italy, 1 day)\n*Victims of the [[Zolit\u016bde shopping centre roof collapse|2013 Zolit\u016bde shopping centre roof collapse]] ([[Latvia]], together with [[Estonia]] and [[Lithuania]])\n*Victims of the [[2014 Soma mine disaster]] (Turkey, 3 days; [[Northern Cyprus]], 2 days; Pakistan, 1 day)<ref>{{cite news|title=National mourning declared in Turkey|url=http://news.az/articles/turkey/88355|accessdate=20 May 2014|newspaper=News.Az|date=14 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pmo.gov.pk/press_release_detailes.php?pr_id=491|title= Pakistan to observe day of mourning solidarity with Turkey|publisher=Prime Ministry of Pakistan|date=2014-05-14|accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref>\n*Victims of the [[2014 Southeast Europe floods]] ([[Serbia]], 3 days; [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], 1 day)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2014/05/20/uk-balkans-flood-idUKKBN0E00Z620140520|title=Serbia declares national mourning, flood toll rises|agency=Reuters|date=2014-05-20|accessdate=2014-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.mk/article_print.php?id=5197&show_logo=true|title=Day of Mourning Today in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serb Republic|publisher=independent.mk|date=2014-05-20|accessdate=2014-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520215852/http://www.independent.mk/article_print.php?id=5197&show_logo=true|archive-date=May 20, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Victims of [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|COVID-19]], ([[China]], [[Italy]], [[Ecuador]] (15 days))<ref>{{cite web |title=\u56fd\u52a1\u9662\u53d1\u5e03\u516c\u544a\uff1a2020\u5e744\u67084\u65e5\u4e3e\u884c\u5168\u56fd\u6027\u54c0\u60bc\u6d3b\u52a8 |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/385241304_428290?_trans_=000014_bdss_dkqgadr |website=[[Sohu]] |publisher=[[China Central Television]] |accessdate=2020-04-04 |language=zh |date=2020-04-03}}</ref> \n[[File:Fallen 44 PNP SAF.jpg|200px|thumb|right|The 44 police officers who perished during the [[Mamasapano clash]]]]\n\n==1800-1899==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 1865\n| 1\n| [[Assassination of Abraham Lincoln|Assassination]] of U.S. President [[Abraham Lincoln]]\n| A National Day of Mourning was held on June 1.<ref>{{cite web |author=The President of the United States of America |title=The Obsequies; President Lincoln's Murder Planned in Canada. One of the Seward Assassins a St. Albans Robber. OFFICIAL DAY OF MOURNING APPOINTED. Progress of the Funeral Cortege from Philadelphia. Demonstrations of the People of New-Jersey. Reception of the Remains in this City...|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1865/04/25/archives/the-obsequies-president-lincolns-murder-planned-in-canada-one-of.html |website=The New York Times |date=April 25, 1865}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=National Day of Mourning, June 1st, 1865. Abraham Lincoln, Died April 15, 186