ates-america |website=The American Presidency Project}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Soviet Union}}\n| 1924\n| 1\n| [[Death and state funeral of Vladimir Lenin|Death]] of Soviet leader [[Vladimir Lenin]]\n| <ref name=Russia/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Duranty |first1=Walter |title=Lenin Dies Of Cerebral Hemorrhage; Moscow Throngs Overcome With Grief; Trotsky Departs Ill, Radek In Disfavor |url=https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/learning/general/onthisday/990121onthisday_big.html |website=The New York Times |date=January 23, 1924}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Second Polish Republic}}\n| 1924\n| At least 1\n| Death of former U.S. President [[Woodrow Wilson]]\n| Wilson called for an independent Polish state in his 1918 [[Fourteen Points]] statement.<ref name=PolandMourning/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==1930s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n| 1934\n| 1\n| Death of former Queen consort [[Emma of Waldeck and Pyrmont|Emma]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Koningin Emma ten grave gedragen |url=https://www.delpher.nl/nl/kranten/view?coll=ddd&identifier=ddd:010238498:mpeg21:p003 |publisher=Nieuwe Tilburgsche Courant |page=3 |language=nl |date=March 31, 1934}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Second Polish Republic}}\n| 1934\n| 1\n| [[Assassination of Bronis\u0142aw Pieracki|Assassination of Interior Minister Bronis\u0142aw Pieracki]]\n| Public shows, concerts, and games were suspended.<ref>{{cite web |title=Zarz\u0105dzenie Ministra Spraw Wewn\u0119trznych z dnia 16 czerwca 1934 r. o czasowym zawieszeniu funkcjonowania przedsi\u0119wzi\u0119\u0107 rozrywkowych z powodu \u017ca\u0142oby narodowej |url=http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP19341370184 |website=prawo.sejm.gov.pl |publisher=Monitor Polski |language=pl |date=1934}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n| 1934\n| 1\n| Death of [[Duke Henry of Mecklenburg-Schwerin|Duke Henry]], prince consort\n| <ref>{{cite web |last1=Blad |first1=Tweede |title=De plechtige uitvaart van Prins Hendrik |url=https://www.delpher.nl/nl/kranten/view?coll=ddd&identifier=ddd:010606180:mpeg21:p005 |publisher=Leeuwarder Courant |page=5 |language=nl |date=July 11, 1934}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Second Polish Republic}}\n| 1935\n| 3\n| Death of Polish statesman [[J\u00f3zef Pi\u0142sudski]]\n| Public shows, concerts, and games were suspended.<ref>{{cite web |title=Zarz\u0105dzenie Ministra Spraw Wewn\u0119trznych z dnia 16 maja 1935 r. o czasowem zawieszeniu funkcjonowania przedsi\u0119wzi\u0119\u0107 rozrywkowych z powodu \u017ca\u0142oby narodowej |url=http://prawo.sejm.gov.pl/isap.nsf/DocDetails.xsp?id=WMP19351140144 |website=prawo.sejm.gov.pl |publisher=Monitor Polski |language=pl |date=May 16, 1935}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}\n| 1936\n| 8\n| Death of King [[George V]]\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Second Polish Republic}}\n| 1938\n| At least 1\n| Death of Armenian Catholic Archbishop of Lviv [[J\u00f3zef Teodorowicz]]\n| <ref name=\"PolandMourning\">{{cite web|title=\u017ba\u0142oby narodowe w Polsce (1924-2012)|url=https://historia.org.pl/2012/03/05/zaloby-narodowe-w-polsce-1924-2012/|website=historia.org.pl|language=pl}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Holy See}}\n| rowspan=2| 1939\n| 9\n| rowspan=2| Death of [[Pope Pius XI]]\n| <ref name=\"PopePiusXI\">{{cite web|title=Death of the pope of peace|date=February 16, 1939|publisher=Catholic Freeman's Journal|url=https://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/146387422|website=trove.nla.gov.au}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Kingdom of Italy}}\n| 1\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Pope's Burial Plans |url=https://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/12097342 |website=trove.nla.gov.au |publisher=The Argus |date=February 15, 1939}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==1940s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n! Country\n! Year\n! Days of mourning\n! Reason\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|Polish government-in-exile}}\n| 1943\n| 26\n| Death of Polish Prime Minister-in-Exile [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Sikorski]]\n| It wa